								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Shabat</title>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex; Sefardi semi-cursive script of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>136 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>308</height>
										<width>225</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>220</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>136 folios (+ 1 modern paper flyleaf at the beginning and 3 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Originally quires of 10 leaves each. Incomplete at the end.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Imperfect at the end. </p>
									<p>First leaf mutilated.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="38" writtenLines="38">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible hard-point ruling. </p>
									<p>Flesh side and hair side distingushable. </p>
									<p>Chapter titles and initial words of sections written in larger characters. </p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso. </p>
									<p>Additions in smaller characters and marginal notes found throughout the manuscript. </p>
									<p>Censor's erasures, e.g. folio 117v. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
